//=============================================================================
// Pinmux Panel - Package View with Live GPIO Status
//=============================================================================
// Features:
// - Visual IC package representation (LQFP/TQFP/BGA)
// - Real-time pin status from GPIO registers (DIR, DAT, MUX, GMUX, AMSEL)
// - Color-coded pins: GPIO In/Out (green/red), Peripheral (blue),
//   JTAG (orange), Power (red), Ground (black), Analog (purple)
// - Detailed tooltips showing pin function, GPIO config, and peripheral mux
// - Pin counts by category displayed in legend
//
// Package pin configurations - maps physical pin to type and GPIO number
// Types: 'power', 'ground', 'gpio', 'fixed', 'analog'
// For GPIO pins, gpioNum indicates which GPIO it maps to (-1 for non-GPIO)
// Data extracted from SysConfig deviceData JSON files

